stylometry: Data mining is looking for patterns and trends in a data set. It is a way to analyze sets of data to use in marketing, profiling companies, etc. It allows a person to look at a set of data and be able to figure out what they are looking out by pulling out trends and patterns that would otherwise have not been seen. In the clustering example we did in class, we took a data set and figured out what cities were like other cities when it came to statisical data such as socioeconmic status, ethnic percentages, etc. This can let us look at cities and decide what to ship/sell there, how many, what to charge, etc. all based upon this data. If something works in one city and it is clustered with another the same plan might work in that city as well.
